#!/bin/sh
# Pre-commit PII scanner. Blocks a commit whose staged changes match a PII
# marker. This repository once published a corpus file listing that carried
# personal data; git history had to be rewritten and the repo recreated. This
# hook is the backstop so that cannot recur silently.
#
# The patterns committed here are non-identifying on purpose -- document-type
# nouns, generic identifier shapes, a user-path shape. Identifying literals (a
# surname, an email, old login/host names, corpus filenames) live in the
# trimitdown-private sibling dir, outside the repo tree, so committing this file
# re-introduces none of the data the migration removed.
#
# Install once per clone:      git config core.hooksPath .githooks
# Emergency bypass (avoid):    git commit --no-verify

set -eu

# The repo root, resolved so it is the MAIN working tree even when the commit
# is made from a linked worktree. --show-toplevel would give the worktree
# itself, and the private pattern file, which is a sibling of the main tree,
# would then not be found -- silently, leaving only the weak patterns below.
# That is not hypothetical: two commits were made that way before it was caught.
# --git-common-dir points at the shared .git for both a plain clone and a
# worktree, so its parent is the main tree in either case.
root=$(dirname "$(cd "$(git rev-parse --git-common-dir)" && pwd)")

# Non-identifying markers, safe to keep in version control.
#   - Russian nouns naming document types, the shape corpus filenames take
#   - 11-12 digit runs: the shape of an INN or SNILS
#   - an email address anywhere in added content
#   - the NAS address (192.168.1.100 and .10 are deliberate placeholders)
#   - any Windows user path
patterns='СНИЛС
Паспорт
ИНН
Свидетельство
Доверенность
Декларация
Квитанция
Выписка
Договор
Справка
Полис
\b[0-9]{11,12}\b
[A-Za-z0-9._%+-]+@[A-Za-z0-9.-]+\.[A-Za-z]{2,}
192\.168\.1\.129
[Uu]sers[/\\][A-Za-z0-9._-]{2,}'

# Identifying literals, kept outside version control. Override with
# TRIMITDOWN_PRIVATE (must match tests/conftest.py's default).
extra="${TRIMITDOWN_PRIVATE:-$root/../trimitdown-private}/pii-patterns.txt"
if [ -f "$extra" ]; then
    patterns="$patterns
$(grep -v '^[[:space:]]*#' "$extra" | grep -v '^[[:space:]]*$' || true)"
else
    # Loudly, because a scanner that quietly lost half its patterns is worse
    # than no scanner: it produces confidence it has not earned. On a clone
    # without the private dir this is expected and harmless -- there is no
    # private data there to protect.
    echo "pre-commit: NOTE - no private pattern file at $extra" >&2
    echo "pre-commit: scanning with the generic patterns only." >&2
fi

# Only added lines (leading +), excluding this hook itself -- it necessarily
# contains the very marker words it scans for.
staged=$(git diff --cached --unified=0 -- . ':(exclude).githooks/pre-commit' \
    | grep '^+' | grep -v '^+++' || true)

hit=$(printf '%s\n' "$patterns" | while IFS= read -r pat; do
    [ -z "$pat" ] && continue
    printf '%s\n' "$staged" | grep -inE -e "$pat" | sed "s|^|[$pat] |" || true
done)

if [ -n "$hit" ]; then
    echo "pre-commit: staged changes look like they contain personal data:" >&2
    printf '%s\n' "$hit" | head -20 >&2
    echo "" >&2
    echo "Review carefully. If it is genuinely a false positive:" >&2
    echo "    git commit --no-verify" >&2
    exit 1
fi

# A binary file defeats the scan above entirely: git prints "Binary files
# differ" and no content reaches grep. The last leak was a text JSONL and would
# have been caught; the same file gzipped would not have been. So newly added
# binaries must be of a type this repository actually expects.
allowed='png|jpe?g|gif|ico|icns|svg|webp|woff2?|ttf|otf'
new_binary=$(git diff --cached --numstat --diff-filter=A -- . \
    | awk '$1 == "-" && $2 == "-" { print $3 }' \
    | grep -ivE "\.($allowed)$" || true)

if [ -n "$new_binary" ]; then
    echo "pre-commit: new binary files of an unexpected type are staged:" >&2
    printf '%s\n' "$new_binary" | head -20 >&2
    echo "" >&2
    echo "Binary content cannot be scanned for personal data. Measurement" >&2
    echo "dumps and corpus data must not enter this repository at all." >&2
    echo "If this really belongs here:" >&2
    echo "    git commit --no-verify" >&2
    exit 1
fi

exit 0
